reviews.text: Great bar with good prices on drinks and food. Outdoor seating is plentiful.

Went here for happy hour, was disappointed with the deals, they only offer $1 off beers which was disappointing.
Ordered an orange crush which didn't taste like an orange crush (used orange juice).
Ambience was nice and a lot of seating.

Decent enough food, but it’s overshadowed by their slow, inattentive service.  It takes at least 4 employees to take care of one order.  20+ minutes until you’ll receive a can of beer. And nobody even brought out the check.
Nice mix of relaxed or high-energy moods, depending on where in the bar you are. The upstairs is fun but potentially treacherous, what with all the flailing and feral youths

This is the whitest bar in the universe. The music here tastes like raisans in potato salad. This is where high school teachers in Disney Channel Original movies would go to after work. Three tracks of their playlist is enough to make you feel the melanin leaving your soul. This bar got an 800 credit score. This is the Wayne's Brothers parody of a white hipster bar. Stay here too long you will spontaneously start calling people "brah." Fun for going on safari to check out how the sunducker crowd lives but not worth more than a gimmicky night out. 3 tuna casseroles out of five.

Prob the best time I had in DC was at this place, super dive and by dive I mean no disrespect, just a cool place that had a killer playlist and good cheap drinks! Great place whether you go with someone, a group, or solo... you're gonna be there and have fun and meet people... mixed crowded, young and old...

Great bar with rooftop vibes - but the rooftop is not an open ceiling but the lighting and height of the ceiling gives that same airy feeling. Dive bar, good for big groups. The downstairs is even good for a date as it’s kind of tight near the window.

Though we enjoyed the vibe here, and the cool beer selection, doesn't seem like this is where you come for yummy, homemade food. I ordered a BBQ bacon cheeseburger.. the presentation was cool, but it was pretty overcooked and lacked any seasoning, even with me specifically asking if they can season it.
Instead, I ended up with some very less than appetizing looking chicken tenders. The fries were pretty tasty.

Great local bar with large variety of cocktails and beer.

Roof deck is open and has even more seating

The prices are super low and and it's great neighborhood dive bar with a great vibe

Great ambiance, good deals (shout out to Paul Rudd Wednesdays), not to mention a unique variety of drinks (e.g. lychee jelly sake). Also, the rooftop is the only place I know of in DC where you can smoke.

Their new trivia is fun too, especially if you’re sick of TriviaMatic questions and need a change.

Lovely friendly place for breakfast. Food was tasty and the coffee great. We loved our time here. We will be back x highly recommend.. we did come back for the evening menu.. lovely chips an I had the lemonade which was lovely xx

The interior design and the outdoor seating are fantastic. It is clean and each table has enough room. It is a dog friendly restaurant described in Google map’s reviews, so we came here on Saturday morning. The waiter who assigned us a table in the outdoor seating was very nice and friendly, but unfortunately, the one who served us was less friendly. I would have gave five stars if he could be a little bit more friendly. I asked water for my dog and he seems not willing to do so. There were other dogs in the restaurant and they all got clean water and nicer water bowl. My dog Lucky did not have that privilege, unfortunately. I ordered Coupe Royale and it was great. The chicken sausages and hashbrown square are recommended. The latte art and animal crackers are cute.

This was one of my friend’s favorite place and i’m glad i was able to stop by. They serve breakfast all day!! The menu has a lot of different options including vegetarian and vegan. Service was great and the food was good too. Solid choice for breakfast and lunch.

Awesome neighborhood modern diner. Can be busy during peak brunch hours but everything I’ve tried here is delicious.

Can also walk in for quick coffee/pastry.

When you walk in you’ll see a pic of Obama having a meal 🍽 at the Coupe. When you have your first meal there then you’ll understand why he was there.

This restaurant is great food, friendly staff, good vibes all around. I like to go here for breakfast 🧇 ☕️ sometimes and I live all the way in Maryland and it’s in D.C, that should say enough.

The food is pretty good. I like their orange chicken. And I am a fan of egg rolls.
And the ppl are friendly.
Decent food at a great price. It would be better if they have a better interior design.

I had orange chicken as my husband encouraged me to try it, it was delicious, price is reasonable (you get a good size portion for little money).

I will definitely eat food from here again.

Let me just say and I’m from Tiktok I’m also a black women . Des needs to be fired . She was mad or jealous that the manager took his order and didn’t go through the line with the employees but thought she was above the manager . It’s disrespectful & she did way to much . Hopefully she got fired because panda don’t need a black women working here who can’t control herself . 🤷🏾‍♀️

Good food - bad portions.

I think it depends on the time of day you go, but i've been here around 12pm, 3pm, and 7pm - and it's always been the same. They skimp out on portions as if you aren't overpaying already for a plate of food. There's also a huge cleanliness issue with the tables and the refreshments area.

Food is good! Just the portions and cleanliness needs to be resolved.

Finding a new place to eat is always an adventure in itself. For a late dinner, we chance upon El Chucho. One cannot go wrong with Mexican cuisine. The menu may be short, but the food is good. I enjoyed a fresh vegetarian burrito with cooked mushrooms and peppers. Although the table ordered a side of rice and beans, I was well satiated with the burrito alone. My sisters ordered different taco dishes: one with seasoned chicken and the other a seared Mahi Mahi. The tacos come in a set of two. Although the shells are petite, the tacos are layered well with fresh ingredients.
EL Chucho has a long list of alcoholic concoctions. Additionally, they feature homemade soda ranging from tropical flavors to mixes with spicy pepper notes.
Overall, the restaurant is pleasant to try. They have plenty of outdoor seating.

Come in here for a drink (or as many as you can handle) but also stay here for the food. Awesome tequila and mezcal served by friendly and knowledgeable bartenders. What more could you ask for.

Haven’t had a bad thing on the menu and the food is usually very quick.

Fun neighborhood spot that is now also open late night.

Service was great. I love the overall vibe of the restaurant. The elote and chips and guacamole are really good. My favorite tacos were the pescado tacos (fried salmon). The flavors were perfect. The asada and pollo tacos needed more flavor. I added guacamole and salsa to them and they were better. The drinks are well made and the menu was great. I’d definitely return to try some other menu items!

Video Review -
IG: eatswithchar
TikTok: charlenequeen
The flavours were ok. Tacos are small but filling.  Too much is going on so you lose the taste of the meat it's all condiments and salsas.  Churros are ok a little too soft for my liking.

Just got to DC and decided we want Mexican fare. Looked at the google reviews and listing and found this great hole-in-the -wall.  What a fantastic place!  They have street side seating so we can enjoy the warm weather.  And the food was the best I think I ever had.  I ordered the dinner feature tacos Birria Quesa tacos and they were fantastic.  The flavors and the portion, there were two big stuffed tacos.  The guacamole was outstanding.  I don’t like extra spice and all of the food I chose was packed with flavor.  You will love this place.

I order Angelico if I don’t want to drive to Pete’s, but that doesn’t mean they’re quicker. I ordered at 5:15 this afternoon. At 5:35 I got an email saying the pizza was “out for delivery.”  Nothing arrived in 40 minutes so I called. “Don’t know why you got that email, the delivery guy is just waiting for one more pizza and he’ll leave.”  5 minutes later, a knock on the door with the pizza. Stone cold.  I’m guessing the email was right and the delivery guy forgot. I think I’ll drive to Pete’s next time.

Customer service needs major improvement. I was giving old pizza, the sauce was already dried up. Decided to try it but was horrible. If you're going to sell slices have some made in a rotating display and not try and make a buck with stale pizza.
My family orders pizza from here quite often as we live nearby.  I have to say the pizza is very yummy. Also the service is good and I would recommend.

I ordered from this place for the first time and really enjoyed it. The reviews made me a little concerned but I am glad I did not listen. I ordered a large portobello mushroom and it was enough for my boyfriend and I. The pizza was very good and the feta on it really pulled the entire pizza together. Usually I prefer my pizzas with red sauce but the veggie ingredients and garlic and herb truly made it very flavorful. I did do pick up so by the time I made it home it wasn’t as hot but it was still good. I did eat the leftovers the next day and popped it in the oven to get it toasted and it tasted just as good. Definitely will order form here again.
HORRIBLE place, they're running over 5 Ghost kitchens and all orders take 30+ minutes.

One of the best stakes I have tried in DC! I went for brunch, prices are fair, really good portion, very tasty food, I loved the drinks and our waitress was super nice. We sat outside, though you can opt to sit inside as well. Really good experience, I have been to the one 14th st so was good to visit this location.
My mom and I had a craving for pizza and stopped in. My mom loved her pizza and I ended up getting the meatball sub. I’d have photos but I ate it in about five seconds.

Have been for brunch and for dinner during the pandemic. They have set up a lot of extra tables that are well-distanced and it feels very safe and comfortable. The food, as always, is great. You can make a reservation online - which may be smart for dinner time on the weekends - but I’ve always been able to find a table at other times.

I’ve also found that their pizza is much better eaten in person than takeaway. Brunch food is really good, would give it 8/10. Try the hash if you can!

Overpriced, crust on bottom seemed undercooked.  Dine in might be better. In their defense, most higher end pizza take out I've had during the pandemic has been pretty lackluster. Sauce seemed a bit too sweet for my taste. The employee who gave me my order was nice.

When my family and I got there it was 11:35, that particular day they opened at 11:30. When we arrived the doors were locked so we looked down at the kitchen where there were woman cooking . We knocked and told them we wanted to dine in the lady was so rude and nasty saying well we not open nobody upstairs and closed the door in my face ! worst experience at this red rocks I suggest everyone go to the one on H street where the customer service is excellent

This was the best Vietnamese food I’ve had in DC itself. We ordered the vegetarian pho and the tofu hot pot, as well as vegetarian summer rolls. Everything came out amazing. We were blown away by how delicious it all was. Highly highly recommend.

Stopped by Pho Viet on 14th St a couple weeks ago. Definitely a calm lowkey spot that is affordable. I decided to get the beef round eye & well done brisket Pho, Summer Rolls with Shrimp, and a mango smoothie with pearls. The food was torch and the service was amazing, I’ll definitely be coming back next time I want some Pho!
Happy and proud to say that I have been a regular for years!!!! Never been disappointed! The pho is absolutely amazing and spicy delicious. The summer rolls are always so fresh so as the Pho.

My last experience here was very unpleasant however my partner and I decided to give it another try and this time they really turned it around. I ordered the extra spicy lemongrass pho with tofu and it was so good! I didn’t even need sriracha this time and only added the hosin sauce. Would definitely recommend this dish to the spicy lovers out there. I’m giving four stars because my partner ordered a dish with shrimp and they don’t offer whole only sliced shrimp which is really crazy based on other pho places we have been. I think offering WHOLE pieces of shrimp not slices will make this a five star place.

Was feeling super sick and a friend decided to bring me some pho from this place because he said they were one of the best in DC , when I placed everything in the bowl, BOOM! A ROACH floated right to the top...very disappointing, do not recommend!

I am Livid, I had such high expectations for this chipotle. They literally delivered dog food from them via Uber eats. How do you screw up an entire order that only had two items. I asked for regular chicken I was sent some chicken that tasted like rotisserie chicken, the rice was softer than a babies bottom. Super mushy and gross. My sons tacos had no chicken on the majority of them. You guys really need to do better, especially for delivery services. This should not be acceptable

This is definitely the worst Chipotle I have been to yet. The workers hung up on me when I asked a simple question, they were out of majority of their products and the employees will literally ignore you talking to them.  Management needs to have a serious intervention with this location...

Been coming here since it opened and usually no issues, but I got home today and my lettuce is so past bad, I might just throw the whole thing out. I didn't mind that they were out of guacamole AND sour cream with 2hrs left until close, but this lettuce?? Just say you're out of it too, sht. It's disgusting.
My take out order was incomplete.  It only contained a scoop of steak and no other toppings. It was disgusting yuck

Shockingly this location continues to lack in customer service and often has signs on the door outlining the items they are out of. Tonight was ridiculous. No Sour Cream, Mild Sauce, or Black means. After ordering I walked up to get a fork and hot sauce and both items were empty. After waiting - forks were brought out.

I’m not sure if they are understaffed but the options are limited - not sure how they are out of the majority of items.

We had ordered from this nice place every week, but today we got a burnt cold pizza with missing ingredient. Yes we got the money back, when I call directly and explained that I was not happy about it. They hung up the phone. I wish they have better management.

First time trying La Villa Pizza and the whole family loved it ! Very quick delivery and the Pizza taste so good !
Update : Our 5 or 6th order so far and it is the only place we order pizza and wings from ! The wings are so good 👍🏾Just love the food
I ordered carry out from there and ordered a cheese pizza and they didn't even put sauce on it and it was reheated.

So good!  Ordered 7 pizzas online directly from the shop (no third party) for a birthday party and they arrived quick and hot!  The pizza was great. Regular cheese, spicy chicken, chicken pesto, pepperoni and even a Hawaiian (I can't stand them but someone loved it). The spicy chicken and chicken pesto were huge hits!  We look forward to ordering again!

This was really good pizza. Clearly fresh ingredients, and pride and care went into it. I was happy. I ordered through Slice. As a fair warning, I think they use grubhub to deliver, so it took maybe 35 minutes to get to me after I got the Slice notification that it was on its way, but that's not their fault. I'll just go pick up next time.

name: WOW Café
vicinity: Mordecai Johnson Administration Building, 2400 6th Street Northwest, Washington

reviews.text: Terrible customer service. Food is just okay.

Decent American restaurant. The pancakes and French toast were okay. The bacon was crispy, the scrambled eggs were moist and fluffy. The coffee was ok but nothing special. The service was very slow because there was only one waitress serving, maybe that's because of the holidays. Overall, this is a decent place with reasonable prices.

Imagine it’s 2-3am and you’re hungry.. Where do you go? DoorDash! It took me a solid 30-45 mins and searching through reviews. I was going to get pizza at a couple different places but the reviews were either bad or nonexistent. I eventually got a pancakes craving and IHOP it was!

I ordered at 3:10am via DoorDash. I got 2 blueberry pancakes, 2 slices of bacon, scrambled eggs, and hash browns. It was a little over $15. My food Arrived around 3:45am, which wasn’t bad. It was sooner than estimated delivery time, which I was happy about.

The packaging was great! They put the blueberry compost and the whip cream in bowls versus on the pancakes. The food container had layers! I hadn’t seen this before. They had the eggs, bacon, and hash browns at the bottom and then the pancakes ok what looks a plastic top. Then another top was over the pancakes!

While eating, quickly came to conclusion that the bacon wasn’t crispy enough for my liking. While they bagged syrup for my pancakes, they didn’t put any salt and pepper for my scrambled eggs or ketchup for my hash browns. My hash browns was shaped rectangularly and tasted decent without ketchup. I did end up adding some syrup but it wasn’t anything like having ketchup. My pancakes were delicious!!!! While there were blueberries in the pancakes, I think it was the blueberry compost that really make it outstanding! I tasted the whip cream but didn’t use it. It wasn’t very sweet. I honestly got full after eating the first pancake, but I couldn’t leave any evidence for my son, who was sleeping lol.

This take out/delivery experience was really good. I enjoyed the food. Besides not having some condiments, I had no complaints. Thanks IHOP for satisfying my late night hunger!

Do not upgrade your pancakes from regular to tres leches. They just give you two sauces to drizzle over them. The rest of the food is pretty average fast food breakfast stuff. I got the sampler with turkey bacon and my friend got it with turkey sausage. So we got half and half for meats.

I had the worst experience I have ever had going to IHOP. We went in greeted by a waitress in inappropriate feet attire for that setting, and her position. She was wearing sliders, and socks I sincerely pitty the restaurant for when her or someone else is injured because of their footwear attire. Secondly when we were asked what to drink they brought our kiddos orange juice out immediately, but took about 20-25 minutes for a cup of coffee.

No issue with our food whatsoever, but the wait time was really long.

Lastly when we were done eating our waitress was no where to be found. Previous ihop locations I have been to allow you to get the tab and pay up front this location did not allow that, so we had to wait for the waitress which proved to also be a long time. She took another customers payment, and then took ours. We gave her a larger bill so she “had to get change”. Went to the back for roughly 15 minutes.

We left her a tip on the table based on the inadequate service we received which she saw. As I was leaving she mumbled “dang no tip?!” To which I stated it’s on the table… and to be honest you took so long with everything including the simplest task of obtaining change that you really do not deserve one. Our family typically gives pretty large tips because we know what it’s like to work as a server however in this case one was not warranted at all;however, we still gave one.

I think she took long on our $30 change in hopes we would just leave, but we waited because… I mean the service was not great.

We ate at many other restaurants during our visit and tipped our servers very well $20,$50, $100 even. So it was definitely her loss.

The IHOP on 14th St. in DC is the worst friggin IHOP I’ve ever been to in my life five different attempts to come in and sit down at 7 o’clock in the morning and the waitress tells me the same thing I’m not ready to serve. This is just friggin ridiculous and unacceptable. Completely unacceptable. How could you not be ready to serve breakfast at 7:30 in the morning when you’re open 24 hours a day I’ve watched it twice just sitting there talking and talking and talking just ridiculous. Another shiftable.

This is for all customers, check your orders before you leave because it can be the wrong order.
They gave me the wrong order 😑
I just got this pizza delivered in this matter. Not sure if it was dropped or what! but I’m really afraid to eat it. I need my money back

I had driven past his place several times over the years, and I figured that someday I would make way over here to get some delicious bread sticks with he awesome pizza sauce that comes with it.  Today was that day, and I set out on my mission to driver on over here and place my order.  So I have never seen a Pizza hit quite like this one, and it's the type of store that mostly caters to carry out orders or delivery I think.  There are no tables inside, nor are there any chairs for people to sit while they are waiting for their order to be prepared.  One other feature is the fact the the place is built like a fortress hat kind of reminded me of hose check cashing places.  Bullet proof glass surrounded the e counter. I guess that's what is necessary on this side of town.  So I placed my order, and stood around for ten minutes playing with my phone.  Soon enough my bread sticks were ready, and I was out the door, and in my car- quickly.  I've already eaten a couple of the bread sticks and they taste good!

I think by now everyone should know if you order there, don't expect your things to be delivered on time or to be delivered at all. Go pick it up.

They probably received so many complaints that they do not answer the phone and the phone line for customer service is disconnected. Even Pizza Hut tried to transfer me to them, but it tells you the line doesn't exist anymore lol.

Pizza was good after I received it and I warmed it up👍.
I am impressed by the length of customer satisfaction this Pizza Hut went. After a mistake I made, they made a way for me to receive my order. Great team on Georgia Avenue Pizza Hut.

name: Subway
vicinity: 3720 Georgia Avenue Northwest Bay E, Washington

reviews.text: Very fresh and great customer service I like it but, I did not like the neighborhood outside it is very unsafe.

I highly recommend going to ANOTHER SUBWAY , the lady worker is so stingy with the food being provided! She barely gives you anything on your sandwich and charges extra for a little bit more ! Save your time and get what your moneys worth SOMEWHERE ELSE!

They have all the chairs and table stacked up and put to the side if your taking away the option why not get rid of the materials instead of being like kids and saying look at this ..one time I seen a guy sitting eating in there tried it for self told no ..food is the same as any subway you make it how you like

I have had more positive experiences than bad. One of the issues I have with this location is that the employees don't understand what I am saying when asking for toppings. There should definitely be more training involved or hands on training. I also hate stale bread! Lately the bread is has been hard as a rock when I eat it. Today I went at 11. Store was dirty (lobby) with vomit in the corner. I think it was vomit. Gross!

Placed an order online for 3 subs and they messed up one of the subs that I added special instructions to place the guacamole separately. The good part was they made my sandwich over. One of the other two subs was a tuna and looks as though they put a scoop each on a footlong. Mind you, it’s suppose to be 2 scoops per 6 inch. So sad that they would skimp on a sub that someone would pay for. If I return to this location, I will have to see them make my sub in person and not order online again.

On 12-1-22 I was at Children’s National Hospital in DC for my daughter who was undergoing  heart surgery. As you can imagine it was very stressful and emotional. On 12-2-22 she was able to talk and developed an appetite. When asked what she wanted for dinner she replied, “CAVA”. No way I would ever deny her request I Goggled the neared CAVA. It indicated the nearest one was located 14th Street DC, Columbia location. My daughter wanted her food a certain way at which I really didn’t understand due to the fact I had never been to a CAVA. Upon my arrival I tried to explain how I wanted the order and was assisted by the manager, later ID as Elmer. I explained to Elmer I needed the order a certain way. I explained the whole situation about my daughter and that I didn’t want to disappoint her. Elmer took his time to complete the order exactly how my daughter requested. Elmer then advised me that he wanted to treat my daughter to the meal. To say the least I was overwhelmed and couldn’t thank him enough for his generosity.I wanted to share this story due to the fact what my daughter had endured over the last 24 hours, Elmer made her feel special out of his own kindness.

CAVA and customers please recognize Elmer for his kind gesture and outstanding service!!!!

A new loyal customer of CAVA

This is my favorite casual dinner place in the city. Not just cava, but this specific branch. Elmer goes out of his way, each time I’m here, to say hello, ask me about my day, and provide exceptional customer service. He’s truly an asset to the team.

The food is fantastic as well. Mix and match locally-sourced toppings and proteins into a bowl or a pita for a reasonable price. In an area with a plethora of food options, cava stands out.

Staff was super rude. I had a pick up order and was waiting for 15 mins for someone to notice me. I finally asked the older female worker and she told me to get it myself. Her tone was nasty not only that but I had to go behind the counter to get it!!! As a restaurant worker it was trivial and childish. All she had to do was pass it to me.

Go-to spot for a quick lunch during the work week, restaurant is always clean and consistently has all menu items available. Shout out to Elmer and the staff at the Columbia Heights location, very friendly and consistently great service.
So delicious and fresh. Good healthy food. And the iced teas are very good too.
The karaoke on Thursday is so fun. We enjoyed the fajitas and the margaritas. Great staff and wonderful people.

Limited menu. My gf got a platter which tasted bad, was not offered a replacement or anything like that, they could only take it back to the kitchen. They still charged us it. Will not come back again.
Haydee’s is a true hidden gem. Go for dinner and get the papusa platter, get a house, peach, or strawberry margarita and enjoy the amazing karaoke. Special place
We were trying to get a refreshing and good drink , sorry but not so good

I LOVE HAYDEES. 🧉🌈🌺🦋✨

Always come and check out the vibe when I’m in town for business. There’s always a myriad of things going on from dance parties to drag shows to karaoke. Food serves late, drinks are abundant and the space is lively. It’s not for the snobby Airbnb tourists, if you don’t like a local restaurant of a place you’re visiting, bashing them on the internet is obnoxiously irritating. I would be rude to snobby tourists too. Get a grip. Lol.

Great place! Easy to order, big selection, and plenty of seating inside and out. Best croissant in DC? I will say it is the only croissant in DC but it was absolutely fantastic and I would be willing to believe it's the best. I would happily go back the next time I am in the area.

Horrible, do not go here! The baked goods are stale! I ordered a pistachio croissant & it was inedible!
I ordered around 3:30pm in store. The croissant was so hard that I could barely break it apart into pieces. It flaked everywhere from how stale & dry it was. I cut it open and there was barely any filling as well. I am so disappointed and will never return, and highly encourage you not to as well.
I put pictures to show how hard the croissant was + the inside of it. They need to do better

Not so french but not so bad. Pastries were hit or miss. Pain au chocolat was good, but flavored cookies were bland, no flavor at all. Chairs and tables were dirty with food crumbs everywhere. Staff was nice and friendly.

Decent breakfast spot. I got the #6 which is eggs, tomatoes, spinach, and cheese on an English muffin. Side of tots with an Orange Juice. It wasn’t what I expected the spinach wasn’t cook just raw spinach and the tomatoes made the sandwich cold. Plus I was given the butt of the tomatoes. The atmosphere was nice and the Orange juice was ok.
Some items, a pie and some cookies, tasted like refrigerator. The croissants and tarts were delicious. The coffees were made well. They have a large assortment of other drinks as well.

Food arrived a hot mess!! Sauce was drizzled on my chicken poppers and no sauce and purchased additional! Plus the pizza wasn’t cut throughly ! Some small slices other big and the garlic sauce was SMOOSHED into pizza! Manager had attitude when I explained grievances!

I don't know what happened to PJs. We were regular customers. But all of a sudden prices increased a lot and the pizzas became very sulky. Barely any tomato sauce (you can see the dough!), and I have to look for the 2 toppings with a magnifying glass, especially the mushrooms. We will give it 1 more go, but if it will be the same, they just lost a customer.

The pizza is fine. The people are idiocracy.  I ordered on the Papa John's app and it said 30-40 minutes. Over 1hr 20 still waiting. Try to call the store 5 times and it auto-disconnects.  Got an operator eventually and she had no record of my order.  Finally got the store and they had no idea what was going on but just assured me my pizza would get there eventually.  Still waiting.

Truly disappointed waited over 3 hours on Superbowl Sunday 🏈 for food 🍕 🍗 to arrive.😱.We were told our order was on the way, but it had never left the store 😡 By the time ⌚ our food arrived the Super Bowl 🏈 was over 🧐 The cheese sticks were hard & cold & didn't look freshly made 😤 The chicken wings were not hot & they had sauce poured over top of them & you could not taste the Parmesan throughout the wings 🍗 nor could you taste the BBQ.. & much of the same with the other order of wings... The pizza 🍕 was okay but it was cold 🥶...Normally I absolutely love Papa John's 💕 but this is my worst experience...I will never purchase anything from this location again...One of the best Papa John's I ever bought food at was on Capitol Hill in Washington, DC that location gets 5 stars🌟🤩🌟 but this one was awful..☹️..smh

The pizza was good, BUT:
- delivery came 45minutes later than scheduled
- pizza was cold
- jalapeño bites were so overstuffed, you couldn’t eat them
- customer service was a nightmare. I called four times and twice they just hung up mid-call, they were unfriendly, one obviously didn’t understand a word I said

Will never order here again.

This is a very nice and comfortable cafe with friendly staff, indoor and outdoor seating, and is also a book and video store. The only thing I suggest is getting a recycling bin for the future. Otherwise, all else was good here.

Awesome gem of a coffee shop, restaurant and book store! I highly recommend getting the chai Frappuccino, it was delicious and not too sweet. The servers were also friendly and warm. This spot also have an amazing outdoor area with a lot of spread out picnic tables and greenery. Will definitely be back!

I knew I had to visit this place and didn’t get a chance to do so for the many trips I took to DC. This time around I made it work; from the moment I stepped in, till I read all I could from all the available books written by or about Black people, till I talked to good people there, grabbed a cool chai latte - an amazing cooler - and had two items of the menu (one vegan one carnivore 😂) and until I said bye - I felt black pride ✊🏾 I felt represented, I felt like I belong, I honestly felt that I needed more of this. It’s very therapeutic and the infotainment is eye opening. Give thanks 🙏🏾 until I come next time either with my own book to put on the shelf or to just grab a coffee - Peace be with you brethren and Sistrens!! ✊🏾

This is like SUPER my kind of place. Hippest coffee joint in DC for sure, I was delighted to find they had fresh fruit smoothies! Something I thought I was sacrificing when I picked Sankofa over a smoothie place down the road, even though I really wanted a fresh fruit smoothie. That's how cool this place is. Great book selection, great crowd, great style, and the food looks like something I WILL try next time I get a chance. Love it.

If you are looking for a bookstore that celebrates Black Culture to the fullest, this is where you need to come! Every single peice of literature in the store, is written and features Black excellence. From children's books to autobiographies, and even science fiction; the genres are all present. They also have a cafe with delicious paninis! The searing area is great for a Spring or Summer day. I highly recommend this bookstore!

There are only 2 things that are consistent about Los Hermanos: The place will be filthy and you will be treated like trash.

Other than that, nothing is ever the same. I go here about once a month. Sometimes I get a huge serving of meats/veggies for $13. Sometimes they barely fill the container and charge me $22. Sometimes the food is fresh. Sometimes the meat is dry and the rice (rice!) has oil pooling on top.

Today for lunch I got a plate of rice, veggies, and quarter chicken. Not a ton of food. Cash register read $15 (already too much). I handed the cashier $20. Then he pressed a button and the total was $22.40 and said that it wasn't enough. I asked why it was so much. No answer. I asked again. He looked out the window ignoring me. So now he has my food and my money. I gave him the extra $3 and left.

IF you decide to eat here, ORDER ONLINE. Don't expect the food to be ready when you get there (it won't), but at least its harder for them to take advantage of you.

When I come here is like eating at home. I had Los Hermanos for a lot of my event and the service is outstanding. Love the food and the staff. Highly recommended. Oh my God and the Chicharrones I love them 🙏🏼🧿

The Dominican food is excellent; however I've had some challenges with the servers.  My coworker who is Dominican turned me on to the spot.  I've always frequented the restaurant with him because he can speak Spanish fluently, I don't speak the language.  I went into the location twice without him and both times, I felt disregarded as a customer and slightly disrespected!  Today, I went in and was completely neglected while the head server packed 4 to go orders in my face, (as if no one was there waiting!).  I asked, hey can someone take my order only to be told wait a minute! A minute literally turned into 15 plus minutes before my order was taken.  Completely unacceptable and bias towards BLACK women! Food is good, but I will go elsewhere from this day forward!

This used to be one of my fav Latino spots in NW but....lately its really "hit or miss" more miss. This morning I ordered a traditional Dominican breakfast: Mangu con queso frito, cebolla roja y chivo. Translation: mashed plantain,  fried Caribbean cheese, red onions and goat. The mangu was not all the way mashed, the goat tasted really bland and like it was going bad, the fried cheese was HORRIBLE it tasted STALE AND LEFT A HORROBLE AFTER TASTE.
Get. It. Together. Nobody wants to pick up food, pay good $ AND bring it home only to be VERY DISSATISFIED AND DISSAPOINTED. 😡.

I have NEVER eaten somewhere and said "this almost tastes exactly like my mom's food." This is the first place to do so. I'm not reviewing the customer service or anything else like others talk about in the google reviews. I am solely talking about the food. With that said, you need to try this place. The portions are large and the food is delicious. Every bit of the dish compliments the other parts of the dish (the meat and the plantains, the rice and the meat, etc.). It is affordable and I 100% will return whenever I'm in the area.
